[
    {
        "text": "Listen up viewers,",
        "start": 5.879,
        "duration": 0.66
    },
    {
        "text": "we’ve got important news for you:",
        "start": 6.539,
        "duration": 1.67
    },
    {
        "text": "One of these days,",
        "start": 8.209,
        "duration": 1.121
    },
    {
        "text": "you’re going to die.",
        "start": 9.33,
        "duration": 0.889
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, hopefully it’s not going to happen today,",
        "start": 10.219,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": "so now that we’ve caught you",
        "start": 11.869,
        "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
        "text": "while living, we want to hit you",
        "start": 12.869,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "with some science so you’re aware",
        "start": 14.369,
        "duration": 1.09
    },
    {
        "text": "of what goes on, after you’re gone.",
        "start": 15.459,
        "duration": 2.181
    },
    {
        "text": "Let’s say hypothetically that you",
        "start": 17.64,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": "were to just slump over dead",
        "start": 18.98,
        "duration": 1.28
    },
    {
        "text": "in your chair right now.",
        "start": 20.26,
        "duration": 1.279
    },
    {
        "text": "So, what happens next?",
        "start": 21.539,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Well, because your heart is",
        "start": 23.039,
        "duration": 1.191
    },
    {
        "text": "no longer pumping, your blood stops",
        "start": 24.23,
        "duration": 1.65
    },
    {
        "text": "flowing and coagulates - forming clots",
        "start": 25.88,
        "duration": 1.949
    },
    {
        "text": "and becoming really thick and lumpy.",
        "start": 27.829,
        "duration": 1.481
    },
    {
        "text": "As as your blood is no longer",
        "start": 29.31,
        "duration": 1.349
    },
    {
        "text": "circulating, it settles where gravity",
        "start": 30.659,
        "duration": 1.67
    },
    {
        "text": "forces it to – a process called",
        "start": 32.329,
        "duration": 1.531
    },
    {
        "text": "post-mortem hypostasis or livor mortis.",
        "start": 33.86,
        "duration": 3.289
    },
    {
        "text": "Without circulation, your body",
        "start": 37.149,
        "duration": 1.391
    },
    {
        "text": "temperature also drops and your muscles",
        "start": 38.54,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "stiffen in the process known as rigor mortis",
        "start": 40.25,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "(onscreen text: Latin for\n“stiffness of death”)",
        "start": 42.69,
        "duration": 0.82
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, obviously you aren’t breathing any more.",
        "start": 43.51,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "No respiration means no oxygen",
        "start": 45.43,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "is getting to your cells.",
        "start": 47.2,
        "duration": 1.11
    },
    {
        "text": "Without oxygen in your cells,",
        "start": 48.31,
        "duration": 1.45
    },
    {
        "text": "the mitochrondria inside can’t",
        "start": 49.76,
        "duration": 1.57
    },
    {
        "text": "make ATP, a chemical used for",
        "start": 51.33,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "a host of cellular tasks.",
        "start": 53.04,
        "duration": 1.99
    },
    {
        "text": "If your cells can’t make ATP,",
        "start": 55.03,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "your cells stop working.",
        "start": 56.89,
        "duration": 1.47
    },
    {
        "text": "In otherwords, you’re dead.",
        "start": 58.36,
        "duration": 1.78
    },
    {
        "text": "With your cells now kaput,",
        "start": 60.14,
        "duration": 1.54
    },
    {
        "text": "they start to break down and release",
        "start": 61.68,
        "duration": 1.149
    },
    {
        "text": "all sorts of stuff including enzymes.",
        "start": 62.829,
        "duration": 2.5
    },
    {
        "text": "That makes for an environment that is",
        "start": 65.329,
        "duration": 1.061
    },
    {
        "text": "very attractive to bacteria and fungi,",
        "start": 66.39,
        "duration": 2.29
    },
    {
        "text": "which eventually enter the mix and",
        "start": 68.68,
        "duration": 1.329
    },
    {
        "text": "start decomposing, or putrefying the body.",
        "start": 70.009,
        "duration": 2.621
    },
    {
        "text": "This process certainly isn’t pretty,",
        "start": 72.63,
        "duration": 1.879
    },
    {
        "text": "but it’s definitely normal.",
        "start": 74.509,
        "duration": 1.481
    },
    {
        "text": "Now before you’re buried or cremated,",
        "start": 75.99,
        "duration": 1.93
    },
    {
        "text": "your family may want a funeral.",
        "start": 77.92,
        "duration": 1.53
    },
    {
        "text": "To slow the decomposition process and",
        "start": 79.45,
        "duration": 1.779
    },
    {
        "text": "keep you looking tidy, chemistry comes",
        "start": 81.229,
        "duration": 1.77
    },
    {
        "text": "in handy via a process called embalming.",
        "start": 82.999,
        "duration": 2.65
    },
    {
        "text": "The embalming process happens in two steps.",
        "start": 85.649,
        "duration": 2.341
    },
    {
        "text": "First, your body is going to be loaded",
        "start": 87.99,
        "duration": 1.379
    },
    {
        "text": "full of preservative chemicals like",
        "start": 89.369,
        "duration": 1.39
    },
    {
        "text": "formaldehyde or glutaraldehyde using",
        "start": 90.759,
        "duration": 1.911
    },
    {
        "text": "a pump and your circulatory system.",
        "start": 92.67,
        "duration": 2.009
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, all your stomach contents get sucked",
        "start": 94.679,
        "duration": 2.241
    },
    {
        "text": "out and all the dark nether regions",
        "start": 96.92,
        "duration": 1.649
    },
    {
        "text": "untouched by the circulatory system",
        "start": 98.569,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "are filled up with the same chemicals.",
        "start": 100.069,
        "duration": 1.76
    },
    {
        "text": "While the embalming process does",
        "start": 101.829,
        "duration": 1.33
    },
    {
        "text": "offer more time for your family to",
        "start": 103.159,
        "duration": 1.291
    },
    {
        "text": "bid farewell to a you that mostly",
        "start": 104.45,
        "duration": 1.699
    },
    {
        "text": "looks like you, it is only temporary,",
        "start": 106.149,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "then it’s back to decomposition.",
        "start": 108.219,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "During the decomposition process,",
        "start": 110.499,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "a huge array of chemical byproducts",
        "start": 112.079,
        "duration": 1.68
    },
    {
        "text": "are spewed out by bacteria.",
        "start": 113.759,
        "duration": 1.28
    },
    {
        "text": "Two in particular, putrecine and",
        "start": 115.039,
        "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
        "text": "cadaverine smell absolutely disgusting,",
        "start": 117.039,
        "duration": 2.021
    },
    {
        "text": "I mean really, they smell like a dead body.",
        "start": 119.06,
        "duration": 3.289
    },
    {
        "text": "Sulfur containing compounds are also",
        "start": 122.349,
        "duration": 1.91
    },
    {
        "text": "produced, which smells like rotten",
        "start": 124.259,
        "duration": 1.13
    },
    {
        "text": "egg and skunk, along with countless",
        "start": 125.389,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "other gases that work together, to",
        "start": 127.099,
        "duration": 1.491
    },
    {
        "text": "temporarily make you more bloated",
        "start": 128.59,
        "duration": 1.55
    },
    {
        "text": "than you ever were while living.",
        "start": 130.14,
        "duration": 1.49
    },
    {
        "text": "Ok, so we’ve heard that some say",
        "start": 131.63,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "that your hair and nails keep",
        "start": 133.73,
        "duration": 1.33
    },
    {
        "text": "growing after you die.",
        "start": 135.06,
        "duration": 1.22
    },
    {
        "text": "But, let’s see what mortician/youtuber",
        "start": 136.28,
        "duration": 2.53
    },
    {
        "text": "Caitlin Doughty from The Order of",
        "start": 138.81,
        "duration": 1.47
    },
    {
        "text": "the Good Death has to say about that.",
        "start": 140.28,
        "duration": 1.81
    },
    {
        "text": "“The hair on your head grows a tiny",
        "start": 142.09,
        "duration": 2.58
    },
    {
        "text": "amount everyday, But when you die",
        "start": 144.67,
        "duration": 3.03
    },
    {
        "text": "those processes stop.",
        "start": 147.7,
        "duration": 2.27
    },
    {
        "text": "For thousands of years,",
        "start": 149.97,
        "duration": 0.91
    },
    {
        "text": "people thought that the dead’s",
        "start": 150.88,
        "duration": 1.62
    },
    {
        "text": "hair and fingernails kept growing",
        "start": 152.5,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "after death, because that’s what",
        "start": 154.59,
        "duration": 1.89
    },
    {
        "text": "it looked like to the naked eye.",
        "start": 156.48,
        "duration": 2.49
    },
    {
        "text": "But it’s not that the hair and nails",
        "start": 158.97,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": "are growing, it’s that the rest of",
        "start": 160.31,
        "duration": 1.97
    },
    {
        "text": "your body is shrinking.",
        "start": 162.28,
        "duration": 2.61
    },
    {
        "text": "When you die, your body dehydrates",
        "start": 164.89,
        "duration": 1.8
    },
    {
        "text": "and the formally moisturized",
        "start": 166.69,
        "duration": 1.84
    },
    {
        "text": "plump skin shrivels.",
        "start": 168.53,
        "duration": 2.73
    },
    {
        "text": "Revealing not growth but what",
        "start": 171.26,
        "duration": 2.81
    },
    {
        "text": "was already there to begin with.”",
        "start": 174.07,
        "duration": 2.3
    },
    {
        "text": "Okay, so now you’ve got a",
        "start": 176.37,
        "duration": 2.05
    },
    {
        "text": "good sense of what happens",
        "start": 178.42,
        "duration": 0.87
    },
    {
        "text": "when you can sense no more.",
        "start": 179.29,
        "duration": 1.16
    },
    {
        "text": "And while it may seem like",
        "start": 180.45,
        "duration": 1.03
    },
    {
        "text": "a dark topic, just remember,",
        "start": 181.48,
        "duration": 1.74
    },
    {
        "text": "live life to the fullest!",
        "start": 183.22,
        "duration": 1.31
    },
    {
        "text": "Learn more chemistry while you",
        "start": 184.53,
        "duration": 0.84
    },
    {
        "text": "still can, do yourself a favor",
        "start": 185.37,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "and hit that subscribe button!",
        "start": 187.29,
        "duration": 1.3
    },
    {
        "text": "And be sure to check out Caitlin’s",
        "start": 188.59,
        "duration": 1.14
    },
    {
        "text": "channel too for more facts about",
        "start": 189.73,
        "duration": 1.31
    },
    {
        "text": "the end of your life. She’s also",
        "start": 191.04,
        "duration": 1.19
    },
    {
        "text": "got an awesome new book out,",
        "start": 192.23,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "the link is in the description below.",
        "start": 193.59,
        "duration": 2.03
    },
    {
        "text": "Click that button to the right",
        "start": 195.62,
        "duration": 0.91
    },
    {
        "text": "to subscribe to her channel.",
        "start": 196.53,
        "duration": 1.48
    },
    {
        "text": "Big shoutout to ACS Webinars",
        "start": 198.01,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "for hooking us up with the",
        "start": 199.59,
        "duration": 0.94
    },
    {
        "text": "chemistry of Death webinar,",
        "start": 200.53,
        "duration": 1.51
    },
    {
        "text": "these folks have got tons",
        "start": 202.04,
        "duration": 1.19
    },
    {
        "text": "of cool chem videos,",
        "start": 203.23,
        "duration": 1.31
    },
    {
        "text": "subscribe to their channel,",
        "start": 204.54,
        "duration": 1.43
    },
    {
        "text": "learn something new, and",
        "start": 205.97,
        "duration": 0.89
    },
    {
        "text": "we’ll see you again soon, chemheads.",
        "start": 206.86,
        "duration": 1.36
    }
]